                </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Price and Launch Timeline: The Road Ahead </h3>
                <p>
                    The success of a new two-wheeler, especially in a new segment, hinges on its pricing. The OLA Cruiser is expected to be a premium offering, but OLA is known for its aggressive pricing strategies. While some reports suggest a price range of <span class="font-weight-700">₹1.5 lakh to ₹2 lakh</span>, other sources indicate a higher price of up to ₹2.7 lakh. Based on its targeted segment and expected features, a realistic ex-showroom price is likely to be between <span class="font-weight-700">₹2.0 lakh and ₹2.5 lakh</span>. This would position it competitively against both high-end electric motorcycles and popular petrol-powered cruisers.<br /><br />
                    As for the launch timeline, the journey for the <span class="font-weight-700">OLA Cruiser</span> has been a bit longer than anticipated. While initially showcased as a concept, OLA has been meticulously working on bringing its electric motorcycle lineup to life. The company has teased the battery packs and has mentioned commencing deliveries in early 2026. Therefore, the OLA Cruiser is expected to make its official debut and launch in the Indian market around <span class="font-weight-700">October 2025</span>. This timeline allows OLA to build on its existing ecosystem and ensure a smooth rollout for a product of this scale and complexity.
                </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Deep Dive into the Expected Specifications</h3>
                <p>As a cruiser, the OLA Cruiser's specifications will be tailored for long-distance comfort and a smooth, effortless ride. Here's a look at what we can expect:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Motor and Performance:</span> The OLA Cruiser will likely be powered by a mid-drive motor, offering a balanced and efficient performance. The power output is expected to be in the range of <span class="font-weight-700">5-8 kW</span>, which would provide a comfortable top speed of around <span class="font-weight-700">100-120 km/h</span>. This is more than sufficient for cruising on highways and provides enough power for quick overtakes. The focus will be on consistent, smooth torque delivery rather than blistering acceleration, in line with the cruiser philosophy. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Battery and Range:</span> The most crucial aspect of an electric cruiser is its range. The OLA Cruiser is expected to come with a large battery pack, likely in the range of <span class="font-weight-700">6-8 kWh</span>. This is a significant jump from the batteries used in electric scooters and is essential for long rides. The company has teased a range of up to <span class="font-weight-700">200 km on a single charge</span> for its motorcycles, which would be a game-changer for the segment. A claimed IDC (Indian Driving Cycle) range could be even higher. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Charging:</span> To support its long-distance capabilities, the OLA Cruiser will need fast charging. It is expected to be compatible with OLA's growing network of Hyperchargers, allowing a quick top-up on the go. A full charge at home with a standard charger is likely to take between <span class="font-weight-700">6 to 8 hours</span>.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Ergonomics and Comfort:</span> A true cruiser is all about the riding experience. The OLA Cruiser is expected to have a well-cushioned, single-piece seat for both rider and pillion, a comfortable handlebar, and forward-set footpegs. The suspension will be tuned for a plush ride over long distances. The chassis will be robust, providing stability at highway speeds.</li>
                </ul>
